OL,6,FHe told them: "There are no words of
OL,7,Fcondolence which I can express which
OL,8,Fwill be adequate to meet the grief and
OL,9,Fsense of loss the family have
OL,10,Fexperienced since the devastating news
OL,11,Fof Amber's death was brought to their
OL,12,Fdoor.
OL,14,F"Nor adequate to bring them some
OL,15,Fcomfort in the many years ahead when
OL,16,Fthey will only have photographs and
OL,17,Fmemories of a young woman killed by
OL,18,Fyou. Their grief and the consequences
OL,19,Fof Amber's death will far exceed the
OL,20,Ftime each of you will spend in
OL,21,Fcustody."
